JUN. 1 6 1998
FEATURED
WINES
Your flight attendant will inform you of today's selections.
White wine
Villa des Pins Vin de Pays d'Oc Chardonnay 1996
Louis Martini California Chardonnay 1995
Red wine
Caliterra Valle Central Merlot 1997
Santa Carolina Maipo Valley Cabernet Sauvignon 1995
DINNER
Appetizer
Scallops with blackened tomatoes and pesto artichoke bottoms
Garden fresh salad
Accompanied by classic Caesar or country French dressing
Sautéed chicken breast with tomato and olive compote
An American favorite accented by a stuffed baked potato
filled with onions, bacon and Parmesan cheese
Maryland crab cakes with a tomato mustard sauce
Originating in the Chesapeake Bay area,
presented with an orzo medley and sugar snap peas with carrots
Penne pasta with Pennsylvania mushroom essence
An American version of an Italian classic,
served with oven-roasted carrots, onions, zucchini and peppers
Midwestern-style grilled veal chop with green peppercorn sauce
Coming from the heartland of America with old-fashioned flavors,
offered with grilled polenta and a vegetable medley
DESSER
BEN&JERRY'S. Vanilla and Strawberry ice cream
STARBUCKS. coffee will be available throughout the flight.
Crystal Geyser Natural Alpine Spring Water
cookies warm from the oven
